data.description: No Metro District ! You'll love this 2014 built home and appreciate the low HOA fee with  great benefits in the Enchantment Ridge Subdivision.  The HOA pays for the exterior water and the lawn mowing of the front and side yards of this property.  Consider this home to be move in ready... the HVAC  was updated in 2022, new carpet on the main floor and stairs this month, and fresh exterior paint. The garage is complete with EV hook up with 240 electric. This 4 bedroom home sits on a corner lot abuts open space to the back.  Just inside the entry of the home, a quiet office space is perfect for those that prefer to work from home.  The unfinished basement is a blank canvas ready to finish now or later with additional bedrooms, a bathroom and a large recreational area.  The floor plan boasts of wood floors, and a lovely open concept that allows an abundance of natural light in the kitchen and living. The primary ensuite bedroom is spacious and private, and has a roomy walk in closets, along with a double sink, light-filled bathroom. This home is situated with an ease to get to downtown Loveland and  highway 287 for entertainment, restaurants and shopping.  Don't miss this one!
